1. Neutrons relesed by fast uncontroled fission can be<br>
 stopped completely by shields of steel iron and lead.<br>
Gamma rays, and x-rays from nuclear explosions can also be completely blocked like the neutrons in this way.<br>
Almost all the energy of a nuclear explosion is released<br>
in the form of X rays. That is why The Hydrogen bombs <br>
physics is based on the principle of radiation implosion, and direct radiation heating of the fusion fuel (The teller-ulam principle.)That is why the 1980s designs for x ray laser weapons pumped by nuclear explosions  were based on this fact too. A few sheets of paper or metal foil can block all alpa, and beta particles. Metals  such as steel lead et el can reflect  em radiation including x rays,radio, waves, microwaves , Uv, Ir ,  and gamma rays too et el.<br>
Tim  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dustyslaunchpad>Dustys Launchpad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/1/03 4:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=319.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: You're right. It's not possible, just because you say so</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Direct radiation declines by the inverse sqaure law.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
